description:
HOME OPEN: Saturday 21st January 1:15pm - 2:00pm

This superb, immaculately presented spacious 4 bedroom, 2 bathroom with study home has everything you need, located only minutes' drive into the Busselton CBD, the local shops, cafes and stunning shores of Geographe Bay. This could be the one you have been waiting for.

You will love the floor plan of this spacious home. Large entry hall and office/study with French doors to the front of the residence through to the open plan family/dining room with recess ceilings, overlooked by the lovely country styled kitchen with quality fittings and plenty of storage space, plus separate games room with French doors. You will be impressed by the very large master suite with great size ensuite, good size minor bedrooms all with built-in robes, reverse cycle ducted air-conditioning and high ceilings throughout and a fantastic undercover alfresco paved entertainment area, great for entertaining your family and friends.

Features Include:
- Manicured front reticulated lawns and gardens
- Light bright gorgeous decor throughout the residence
- Large entry hallway with recessed ceiling and shoppers entrance way from the garage
- Good size office/study with French doors leading off the hallway perfect for the home business
- Massive master suite with walk-in robe and great size ensuite with double vanity, shower and spa bath, separate WC
- Wood-look tiling, high ceilings and zoned reverse cycle air-conditioning throughout
- A well-appointed spacious country styled kitchen with 5 burner gas stove and electric oven, walk-in pantry and plenty of cupboard and bench space, dishwasher
- Elegant dining area and family area with recessed ceilings
- Separate carpeted living room with French doors and a bay window
- 3 great sized minor bedrooms all with double built-in robes
- Main bathroom with shower, spa bath and vanity
- Separate laundry and hallway storage cupboards
- Solar hot water system with instantaneous gas back up
- Gas bottles
- North facing paved undercover alfresco dining with ceiling fan and adjoining pergola
- 6 solar panels
- 5m x 3m garden shed

This home has plenty of space and some great areas to relax in and enjoy. The perfect family haven or a great investment for the astute buyer.

For further information or to arrange a viewing, contact your Local Listing Agent Michelle Radich on 0417 986 961.

This information has been prepared to assist solely in the marketing of this property. While all care has been taken to ensure the information provided herein is correct, we do not take responsibility for any inaccuracies. Accordingly, all interested parties should make their own enquiries to verify the information.
